==English==
===Etymology===
From Old (and mdoern) French [[#French|dune]], from Middle Dutch [[#Middle Dutch|dūne]] (Dutch [[duin]]), from Celtic.  Compare [[down]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/dju:n/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːn|-uːn]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A ridge or [[hill]] of [[sand]] piled up by the wind.

===Synonyms===
*[[sand-dune]]

